<div class="artwork-content">

        <div id="artwork-image">
            <img src="images/172147_1327600.jpg" alt="The Wonders of Fascist Photography" title="Nikolai Ernestovich Radlov
(Born St. Petersburg, 1889; died Moscow [?], 1942)
Litbrigade
(Russian, founded 1941), The Wonders of Fascist Photography"  />          </div>

    <p class="tools">
                          <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/TASS/artwork/205616/email"><strong>Email</strong> to a friend</a><br />
                    <a href="http://www.artic.edu/aic/collections/exhibitions/TASS/artwork/205616/print" target="_blank"><strong>Print</strong> this page</a>          </p>
    <!--/tools-->
  
    <div id="artwork-details">
    <div id="tombstone">

    <p>    Nikolai Ernestovich Radlov<br />
(Born St. Petersburg, 1889; died Moscow [?], 1942)<br />
Litbrigade<br />
(Russian, founded 1941)<br />
    </p>
    <h3><em>The Wonders of Fascist Photography</em>, TASS No. 0060, July 12, 1941</h3>

    <p>
    Gouache over carbon-transfer drawing and incising with evidence of secondary layer of graphite in some areas and stenciled letters (panel four).<br />    Each panel: 640 x 880 mm (text panels are missing)<br />    1: First the assignment<br />
2: Then they dress up.<br />
3: Now - Attention!<br />
4: The fruits of their efforts.<br />
<br />
They are typical fascists,<br />
The most criminal specialists.<br />
<br />
They print copies by the thousands;<br />
It's not magic, just sleight of hand.<br />    The Museum of Modern Art, New York, P396.a-d</p>
        
        <!--<p id="dept-gallery">--><!--<br />-->
         <!--</p>-->
    </p>
    </div><!--/tombstone-->

